body: @AdjacentGaming: Going by this book alone, Jun expects Maidashi to be under his thumb because the protag knows the only reason he was able to get with Koharu was because of Jun's help. Jun's last line literally translates to "I'm expecting lots of gratitude from you, (step)dad".

@Moroboshi what a fucking twist if that’s true. I mean just looking at the final panel, the kid seems a little too happy/eager to have a new stepdad, the heart icon makes it seem a little suspicious. What exactly does the kid mean by “cashing in for a long time to come?” oh and mother/daughter stuff is very common in hentai so I believe it lmao

Hello, I'm the translator of this thing. For those confused about Jun's sex: Mitarashi Kousei apparently published a 4-page leaflet last year (2021) as a follow up revealing that Koharu lied to protag about Jun, and instead of being her son is actually her daughter (who also wants to do it with protag). I'm not sure if the artist was just randomly doing it just to do the "afterwards, they all fucked" meme or if he was planning this all along. I'm still not sure what to think since Koharu Biyori was published in 2015, so there's a 6-year gap to account for. Should also note that the leaflet is labeled as a side-story instead of a direct sequel. The leaflet is called "Koharu Biyori Side Story -Koharu and Jun's Secret-".
